.TH SHAPE2TRIANGLE 1 "2026-05-02" "smartmet-shapetools" "SmartMet Tools"
.SH NAME
shape2triangle \- convert an ESRI shapefile to PSLG files for Triangle
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shape2triangle
.I arealimit
.I shapefile
.I outname
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B shape2triangle
reads an ESRI shapefile, discards polygons whose geographical area is
smaller than
.IR arealimit
square kilometres, and writes a Planar Straight Line Graph (PSLG) in
the format expected by Jonathan R.\& Shewchuk's
.B triangle
program. Two files are produced:
.IR outname .node
(the unique vertices) and
.IR outname .poly
(the edges and one inside\(hypoint per polygon).
.PP
Each polygon is given a unique attribute, so triangles produced by a
later constrained Delaunay triangulation can be identified as
belonging to the same original polygon. This is the first step of the
shapetools amalgamation pipeline; see
.BR amalgamate (1)
for the full sequence.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I arealimit
Minimum polygon area in square kilometres; smaller polygons are
dropped. Use
.B 0
to keep every polygon.
.TP
.I shapefile
The input shapefile, given without the trailing
.I .shp
suffix.
.TP
.I outname
Stem for the output PSLG files
.RI ( outname .node ", " outname .poly ).
.SH EXAMPLES
Prepare a Finnish coastline for triangulation, dropping islands smaller
than 5 km\(S2:
.PP
.RS 4
shape2triangle 5 ESRI/Suomi/ponet suomi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR triangle2shape (1),
.BR amalgamate (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Finnish Meteorological Institute
.PP
Report issues at <https://github.com/fmidev/smartmet-shapetools/issues>.
